true crime drama titled ''Far North.'' \n\n==Personal life==\nButler resides with his wife Irina and two children in the [[Woodland Hills, Los Angeles|Woodland Hills]] section of Los Angeles.<ref name=\"BA\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|nm2530433}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Butler, Nathin}}\n[[Category:Male actors from Queensland]]\n\n\n{{Australia-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nathin_Butler"}
{"title_page": "Henri (2013 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Henri\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Yolande Moreau]]\n| producer       = Julie Salvador<br>[[Jacques-Henri Bronckart]]<br>Olivier Bronckart<br>Christophe Jeauffroy<br>Jean-Louis Livi<br>Antonino Lombardo<br>Arlette Zylberberg\n| writer         = Yolande Moreau\n| starring       = [[Pippo Delbono]]<br>[[Miss Ming]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Philippe Guilbert\n| editing        = Fabrice Rouaud\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|5|24|Cannes|2013|12|4|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 103 minutes\n| country        = Belgium<br>France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = $5.6 million<ref name=\"BoxOffice\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=13883 |title=Henri |date=5 February 2014 |accessdate=5 February 2014 |work=jpbox}}</ref>\n| gross          = $1.1 million<ref name=\"BoxOffice\"></ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Henri''''' is a 2013 Franco-Belgian [[drama film]] directed by [[Yolande Moreau]]. It was screened in the [[Directors' Fortnight]] section at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Cannes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/readResonnances/59683.html |title=List of films in Cannes Directors' Fortnight |date=24 May 2013 |accessdate=24 May 2013 |work=Cannes |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922092738/http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/readResonnances/59683.html |archivedate=22 September 2013  }}</ref> The film received four nominations at the [[5th Magritte Awards]], including [[Magritte Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and [[Magritte Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for Yolande Moreau.<ref>{{cite news|title=Magritte: Pluie de nominations pour les Dardenne et Lucas Belvaux|url=http://www.lalibre.be/culture/cinema/magritte-pluie-de-nominations-pour-les-dardenne-et-lucas-belvaux-54ad67193570d587e329a142|accessdate=11 January 2015|work=La Libre Belgique|date=7 January 2015|language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Pippo Delbono]] as Henri Salvatore\n* [[Miss Ming]] as Rosette\n* [[Jackie Berroyer]] as Bibi\n* [[Simon Andr\u00e9]] as Ren\u00e9\n* [[Lio]] as Rita\n* [[Gwen Berrou]] as Laetitia\n* [[Yolande Moreau]] as Aunt Mich\u00e8le\n* [[Philippe Duquesne]] as Jean-Lou\n* [[Isabelle de Hertogh]] as Laetitia's friend\n* [[Brigitte Mariaulle]] as Madame Monnier\n* [[Renaud Rutten]] as Roland\n* [[Pascal Demolon]] as Jean-Pierre\n* [[No\u00ebl Godin]] as The pigeon friend\n* [[Wim Willaert]] as The cop\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2865688|Henri}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Henri}}\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2013 drama films]]\n[[Category:Belgian films]]\n[[Category:Belgian drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n{{Belgium-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Henri\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Yolande Moreau]]\n| producer       = Julie Salvador<br>[[Jacques-Henri Bronckart]]<br>Olivier Bronckart<br>Christophe Jeauffroy<br>Jean-Louis Livi<br>Antonino Lombardo<br>Arlette Zylberberg\n| writer         = Yolande Moreau\n| starring       = [[Pippo Delbono]]<br>[[Miss Ming]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Philippe Guilbert\n| editing        = Fabrice Rouaud\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|5|24|Cannes|2013|12|4|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 103 minutes\n| country        = Belgium<br>France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = $5.6 million<ref name=\"BoxOffice\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=13883 |title=Henri |date=5 February 2014 |accessdate=5 February 2014 |work=jpbox}}</ref>\n| gross          = $1.1 million<ref name=\"BoxOffice\"></ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Henri''''' is a 2013 Franco-Belgian [[drama film]] directed by [[Yolande Moreau]]. It was screened in the [[Directors' Fortnight]] section at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Cannes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/readResonnances/59683.html |title=List of films in Cannes Directors' Fortnight |date=24 May 2013 |accessdate=24 May 2013 |work=Cannes |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922092738/http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/readResonnances/59683.html |archivedate=22 September 2013  }}</ref> The film received four nominations at the [[5th Magritte Awards]], including [[Magritte Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and [[Magritte Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for Yolande Moreau.<ref>{{cite news|title=Magritte: Pluie de nominations pour les Dardenne et Lucas Belvaux|url=http://www.lalibre.be/culture/cinema/magritte-pluie-de-nominations-pour-les-dardenne-et-lucas-belvaux-54ad67193570d587e329a142|accessdate=11 January 2015|work=La Libre Belgique|date=7 January 2015|language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Pippo Delbono]] as Henri Salvatore\n* [[Miss Ming]] as Rosette\n* [[Jackie Berroyer]] as Bibi\n* [[Simon Andr\u00e9]] as Ren\u00e9\n* [[Lio]] as Rita\n* [[Gwen Berrou]] as Laetitia\n* [[Yolande Moreau]] as Aunt Mich\u00e8le\n* [[Philippe Duquesne]] as Jean-Lou\n* [[Isabelle de Hertogh]] as Laetitia's friend\n* [[Brigitte Mariaulle]] as Madame Monnier\n* [[Renaud Rutten]] as Roland\n* [[Pascal Demolon]] as Jean-Pierre\n* [[No\u00ebl Godin]] as The pigeon friend\n* [[Wim Willaert]] as The cop\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2865688|Henri}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Henri}}\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2013 drama films]]\n[[Category:Belgian films]]\n[[Category:Belgian drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n{{Belgium-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\