13 multiple episodes (also ''Ghost Hunters'' live specials host)\n* [[Meat Loaf]] \u2013 \"A Bat Out of Hell\" episode & \"Sloss Furnaces\" episode\n* [[Elijah Burke]] \u2013 \"2007 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Colin Ferguson (actor)|Colin Ferguson]] \u2013 \"USS ''Hornet''\" episode\n* [[Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files|Ben Hansen]] \u2013 \"2010 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Kofi Kingston]] \u2013 \"2010 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Nene Leakes]], Shere\u00e9 Whitfield and [[Kim Zolciak]] \u2013 \"T.A.P.S. Meets ''[[The Real Housewives of Atlanta]]''\" episode\n* [[Hollywood Treasure|Joe Maddalena]] \u2013 \"2010 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Eddie McClintock]] \u2013 \"Ghost of Buffalo Bill\" episode\n* [[The Miz|Mike \"The Miz\" Mizanin]] \u2013 \"2008 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[CM Punk]] \u2013 \"2006 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Meaghan Rath]] \u2013 \"2010 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Allison Scagliotti]] \u2013 \"2010 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Amanda Tapping]] \u2013 \"2008 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Steve Valentine]] \u2013 \"2008 Halloween Special\" episode\n* [[Meredith Vieira]] \u2013 \"Murdered Matron\" episode\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Series overview==\n===Episodes===\n{{Main|List of Ghost Hunters episodes}}\n{{:List of Ghost Hunters episodes}}\n\n==Reception==\n===Success and growth===\n''Ghost Hunters'' has garnered some of the highest ratings of any Syfy reality programming.<ref>[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/pr.aspx?id=20051020scifi0 SciFi Network Ratings Release]</ref> From the start, the show has found an audience for its mix of paranormal investigation and interpersonal drama. It has since been syndicated on [[NBC Universal]] sister cable channel [[Oxygen (TV network)|Oxygen]] and also airs on the Canadian cable network, [[Outdoor Life Network|OLN]].\n\nIn the early shows, TAPS was headquartered in a trailer located behind Jason Hawes' house, and they drove one white van to investigations. Within one season, they had moved the entire operation to a storefront in [[Warwick, Rhode Island]], and acquired several new TAPS vehicles.\n\nIn addition to their successful television venture, TAPS operates a website where they share their stories, photographs, and [[ghost hunting]] videos with an ever-growing membership list. Because of the popularity of the show, TAPS cast members have signed contracts with at least two talent agencies, Escape Artistry and GP Entertainment, to manage their appearances at lectures, conferences and public events.\n\nIn addition to the success of the series, TAPS has ventured into the venue of radio broadcast, hosting a three-hour weekly show called ''Beyond Reality''. New episodes are broadcast every Saturday from 7 pm to 10 pm [[Eastern Time]], though sometimes may skip a week due to the possibility of the hosts being busy with other ventures. The radio show covers topics in a vast array of areas such as [[cryptozoology]], [[spiritualism]], [[ufology]], and [[ghost]]s. The show is hosted by Grant Wilson and Jason Hawes, and includes guest appearances from other TAPS members and special guests such as [[John Zaffis]], Rosemary Ellen Guiley, Chris Fleming, and others who specialize in certain fields. Noted paranormal author Jeff Belanger and ''Spooky Southcoast'' radio host and author Tim Weisberg served as fill-in hosts for Jason and Grant. The show also once simulcasted on ''Spooky Southcoast'', airing from the Mt. Washington Hotel in New Hampshire.\n\nOn March 3, 2010, ''Ghost Hunters''' 100th episode aired featuring their investigation of [[Alcatraz]] Prison. The two-hour special featured a live studio audience with question and answer segments, hosted by [[Josh Gates]] of ''[[Destination Truth]]''. The special also featured the ''[[Ghost Hunters International|GHI]]'' crew, the winning contestants of ''[[Ghost Hunters Academy]]'', and Craig Piligian, the creator and executive producer of ''Ghost Hunters''. On June 2, 2011, Syfy renewed ''Ghost Hunters'' for an eighth season, marking it as the longest-running reality series to air on the network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetvratings.com/2011/06/02/cancelled-renewed/ghost-hunters-renewed-for-season-8-by-syfy/|title=\"Ghost Hunters\" Renewed For Season 8 By Syfy|accessdate=October 1, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427135411/http://insidetvratings.com/2011/06/02/cancelled-renewed/ghost-hunters-renewed-for-season-8-by-syfy|archive-date=April 27, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn June 7, 2016, Hawes announced that ''Ghost Hunters'' would be concluding on Syfy with season 11 being the last season to be produced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/jason-hawestaps/ghost-hunters-leaving-syfy/10153794588723212|title=Ghost Hunters leaving Syfy!|website=www.facebook.com|access-date=June 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn June 26, 2019, it was announced that the series would be [[revival (television)|revived]] later that year with Wilson returning with a new team. The 12th season, initially reported to consist of 20 episodes (later broadcast as 11 with 2 specials, with a 13th season premiering later<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wilson|first=Grant|title=The season finale of @GhostHunters is tonight at 10pm ET/PT! What does that mean for the future of the show???? Watch the video and find out! @aetv #GhostHunterspic.twitter.com/8mlnO0cY8x|url=https://twitter.com/grantswilson/status/1189643297490374656|work=@grantswilson|date=October 30, 2019|access-date=November 5, 2019|language=en}}{{Cite web|last=Wilson|first=Grant|title=The season finale of @GhostHunters is tonight at 10pm ET/PT! What does that mean for the future of the show???? Watch the video and find out! @aetv #GhostHunterspic.twitter.com/8mlnO0cY8x|url=https://twitter.com/grantswilson/status/1189643297490374656|work=@grantswilson|date=October 30, 2019|access-date=November 5, 2019|language=en}}</ref>), premiered on August 21, 2019, on [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] and ended on to October 30, 2019.<ref name=\"GH Return\">{{cite web|title=A&E Network Returns to Paranormal Programming with New Shows Including the Return of \"Ghost Hunters\" with Original Team Leader Grant Wilson|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/26/aande-network-returns-to-paranormal-programming-with-new-shows-including-the-return-of-ghost-hunters-with-original-team-leader-grant-wilson-109212/20190626aande01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 26, 2019}}</ref> Lead investigator and producer Grant Wilson confirmed prior to the October 30, 2019 episode that ''Ghost Hunters'' will return in 2020 for a 13th season of an unspecified number of episodes.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wilson|first=Grant|title=The season finale of @GhostHunters is tonight at 10pm ET/PT! What does that mean for the future of the show???? Watch the video and find out! @aetv #GhostHunterspic.twitter.com/8mlnO0cY8x|url=https://twitter.com/grantswilson/status/1189643297490374656|work=@grantswilson|date=October 30, 2019|access-date=November 5, 2019|language=en}}{{Cite web|last=Wilson|first=Grant|title=The season finale of @GhostHunters is tonight at 10pm ET/PT! What does that mean for the future of the show???? Watch the video and find out! @aetv #GhostHunterspic.twitter.com/8mlnO0cY8x|url=https://twitter.com/grantswilson/status/1189643297490374656|work=@grantswilson|date=October 30, 2019|access-date=November 5, 2019|language=en}}</ref> On February 18, 2020, it was announced that the 13th season will premiere on April 8, 2020<ref>{{cite web|title=A&E Investigates the Paranormal This April with the Spine-Tingling Premiere of Newly Reimagined \"Celebrity Ghost Stories\" and Season 2 of \"Ghost Hunters\"|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2020/02/18/aande-investigates-the-paranormal-this-april-with-the-spine-tingling-premiere-of-newly-reimagined-celebrity-ghost-stories-and-season-2-of-ghost-hunters-609312/20200218aande01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Criticism===\n''Ghost Hunters'' has attracted various critics and skeptics, such as [[Joe Nickell]] of the Committee for Skeptical Inquiry, ''[[Skeptical Inquirer]]'' author [[Lynne Kelly (science writer)|Lynne Kelly]],<ref name=crit1>{{cite book|author=Kelly, Lynne|authorlink=Lynne Kelly (science writer)|title=The Skeptic's Guide to the Paranormal|publisher=Basic Books|year=2005|isbn=978-1-56025-711-0}}</ref> [[James Randi]], and [[Benjamin Radford]]. The Skeptical Analysis of the Paranormal Society (SAPS) was founded with the intent to recreate and debunk segments of the show.<ref name=\"eSkeptic\">{{cite news|first=Alison|last=Smith|title=TAPS vs. SAPS: The Atlantic Paranormal Society meets the Skeptical Analysis of the Paranormal Society|url=http://www.skeptic.com/eskeptic/06-08-10|work=eSkeptic|publisher=[[The Skeptics Society]]|issn=1556-5696|date=August 10, 2006|accessdate=March 22, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2008, ''Ghost Hunters'' was awarded The Truly Terrible Television (TTTV) Award by [[Independent Investigations Group]] for peddling [[pseudoscience]] and [[superstition]] to its audience.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iigwest.com/iigawards/index.html#terrible|title=IIG &#124; The IIG Awards|publisher=Iigwest.com|date=June 23, 2008|accessdate=July 31, 2012}}</ref>\n\nDuring the seven-hour-long, live Halloween show on October 31, 2008, at least two events took place that critics{{who|date=November 2019}} have scrutinized: One occurs when lead investigator Grant Wilson has his jacket collar pulled down by an unseen force three times; all the while one of his hands remained at his side, which led detractors to claim he was pulling a hidden string. This happens again at one point where Hawes touches Wilson's back and his collar moves down again. Another occurs when a supposed disembodied voice tells the hunters, \"You're not supposed to be here.\" Critics{{who|date=November 2019}} have claimed the voice sounded like it was piped in from an external audio source. In regard to the scrutiny, Wilson and Hawes defended themselves, stating that everything in the show is real.<ref name=\"cliqueC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cliqueclack.com/tv/2008/11/14/was-the-coat-pull-on-ghost-hunters-live-event-faked/|title=Archived copy|accessdate=April 7, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090421123443/http://www.cliqueclack.com/tv/2008/11/14/was-the-coat-pull-on-ghost-hunters-live-event-faked/|archivedate=April 21, 2009}} TAPS Interview</ref> In a 2013 interview on ''The Reveal,'' Wilson stated that their television contracts forbade them from faking evidence on the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thereveal.podomatic.com/entry/2013-01-26T10_40_52-08_00|title=Grant Wilson 75 minute long Interview Jan 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2019, Steve Gonsalves from ''Ghost Hunters'' along with Chris Smith and Mike Goncalves of the TV show Haunted Towns hosted a \u201cDeath Ship Ghost Hunt\u201d as part of Ghost Hunt Weekends on the USS North Carolina. Paranormal researcher Kenny Biddle wrote an article for ''[[Skeptical Inquirer]]'' addressing the criticism this event received stating that it could tarnish the reputation of this historical site.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Biddle |first1=Kenny |title=Celebrity Ghost Hunts At Historical Locations |url=https://skepticalinquirer.org/exclusive/celebrity_ghost_hunts_at_historical_locations/?/specialarticles/show/celebrity_ghost_hunts_at_historical_locations |website=skepticalinquirer.org |publisher=[[Skeptical Inquirer]] |accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Method ====\n\nAccording to investigator Benjamin Radford, most ghost hunting groups including TAPS make many methodological mistakes. \"After watching episodes of ''Ghost Hunters'' and other similar programs, it quickly becomes clear to anyone with a background in science that the methods used are both illogical and unscientific\". Anyone can be a ghost investigator, \"failing to consider alternative explanations for anomalous ... phenomena\", considering emotions and feelings as \"evidence of ghostly encounters.\" \"Improper and unscientific investigation methods\", for example, \"using unproven tools and equipment\", \"sampling errors\", \"ineffectively using recording devices\" and \"focusing on the history of the location...and not the phenomena.\" In an article for ''Skeptical Inquirer'', Radford concludes that ghost hunters should care about doing a truly scientific investigation: \"I believe that if ghosts exist, they are important and deserve to be taken seriously. Most of the efforts to investigate ghosts so far have been badly flawed and unscientific \u2014 and not surprisingly, fruitless.\"<ref>{{cite journal |last=Radford |first=Benjamin |date=November\u2013December 2010 |title=Ghost-Hunting Mistakes: Science and Pseudoscience in Ghost Investigations |journal=[[Skeptical Inquirer]] |publisher=Committee for Skeptical Inquiry |volume=34 |issue=5 |pages=44\u201346}}</ref> In a ''[[New York Times]]'' article about ''Ghost Hunters'' and TAPS, Radford contended that \"the group and others like it lack scientific rigor and mislead people into thinking that their homes are haunted.\"<ref name='NYT'>{{cite news|first=BRIAN|last=STELTER|title=\u2018Ghost Hunters\u2019 Seeks Spirits and Ratings|date=November 10, 2009|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/11/11/arts/television/11ghost.html?_r=2&scp=1&sq=ghost%20hunters&st=cse|work=The New York Times|accessdate=February 4, 2012|quote=Benjamin Radford, the managing editor of Skeptical Inquirer magazine, says the group and others like it lack scientific rigor and mislead people into thinking that their homes are haunted. \u201cI\u2019ve seen first-hand some of the damage that the show can do to fragile people who are scared and looking for a real explanation to their experiences,\u201d said Mr. Radford, who also investigates ghostly claims.}}</ref>\n\nThe show's editing has been questioned, such as activity that is not captured on tape and findings that are unsupported by evidence in the show specifically. Tools are used in ways that are not proven effective, or in ways in which they have been proven ineffective, such as [[IR thermometer|infrared thermometers]] that are claimed to detect cold spots in the middle of rooms when such tools are able only to measure the surface temperature of objects.<ref name=\"eSkeptic\"/>\n\nTechniques with thermal imaging cameras, [[Geiger counters]], [[electronic voice phenomenon]], and [[Electromagnetic fluctuation|EMF]] detectors are used with little or no explanation as to how the techniques have proven to provide evidence of ghosts or other entities. There are concerns that the devices are misused, such as the noting of Benjamin Radford's article for ''Skeptical Inquirer'': \"you may own the world's most sophisticated thermometer, but if you are using it as a barometer, your measurements are worthless. Just as using a calculator doesn't make you a mathematician, using a scientific instrument doesn't make you a scientist.\"<ref name=\"crit2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/shady-science.html|title=Reality Check: ''Ghost Hunters'' and \u2018Ghost Detectors\u2019|accessdate=September 24, 2009|last=Radford|first=Benjamin|date=November 12, 2004|publisher=[[Committee for Skeptical Inquiry]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219170632/http://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/shady-science.html|archivedate=December 19, 2007}}</ref>\n\n==Popular culture==\n''Ghost Hunters'' helped popularize [[paranormal television]] and [[ghost hunting]] during its original run.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Craven |first1=Scott |title=Why those TV ghost-hunting shows are transparently fake |url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/travel/arizona/2017/10/02/ghost-hunting-shows-fake/705566001/ |website=[[AZ Central]] |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=CNN |first1=John Blake |title=Ghost hunters haunted by new terror: competition |url=https://www.cnn.com/2013/09/07/us/ghost-hunters-haunted-by-new-terror-competition/index.html |website=CNN |accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref>  For much of its initial airing on Syfy, it was the top-rated paranormal reality show on television. John Blake of [[CNN]] opined in 2013 that ''Ghost Hunters'' \"is to the paranormal field what [[Sugarhill Gang|Sugarhill]]'s \"[[Rapper's Delight]]\" is to hip-hop...\" <ref>{{cite web |last1=CNN |first1=John Blake |title=Ghost hunters haunted by new terror: competition |url=https://www.cnn.com/2013/09/07/us/ghost-hunters-haunted-by-new-terror-competition/index.html |website=CNN |accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nJason and Grant and ''Ghost Hunters'' were parodied on the 2009 episode of ''[[South Park]]'' entitled [[Dead Celebrities]]. They have made [[talk-show]] appearances on the [[List of Late Night with Conan O'Brien episodes (season 13)|December 8, 2005 episode]] of ''[[Late Night with Conan O'Brien]]'', the [[The Ellen DeGeneres Show (season 4)|Oct 31, 2006 episode]] of ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', a 2008 episode of ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]''<ref>{{cite web |title=Grant Wilson & Jason Hawes on The View! |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_xr5wcXYfro |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref>, and the [[List_of_Late_Night_with_Jimmy_Fallon_episodes_(2010)#October|October 28, 2010 episode]] of ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.\n\n== Related productions ==\n=== Spin-offs ===\n==== ''Ghost Hunters International'' ====\n{{Main|Ghost Hunters International}}\n\nA [[media spin-off|spin-off]] series premiered on January 9, 2008, featuring investigators Robb Demarest, Brian Harnois, Donna LaCroix, Andy Andrews, Shannon Sylvia, and Barry Fitzgerald (who appeared in the summer 2007 Ireland episodes of ''Ghost Hunters'') since the onset along with other rotating members from the TAPS family.<ref>[http://www.the-atlantic-paranormal-society.com/abouttaps/members.html Current list of TAPS members] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509170710/http://www.the-atlantic-paranormal-society.com/abouttaps/members.html|date=May 9, 2008}}</ref> The format is similar to ''Ghost Hunters'' but features investigations in various locations around the world.\n\n==== ''UFO Hunters'' ====\n\n''Ghost Hunters'' producers Craig Pilligan and Tom Thayer released another paranormal investigation \"special\" titled ''UFO Hunters'', (not to be confused with the show of the [[UFO Hunters|same name]] which aired on the [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History Channel]]), which first aired on January 30, 2008, however the show only aired one episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/history-and-sci-fi-move-dueling-ufo-hunters-debuts-jan-30-6465.php|title=History and Sci-Fi to air Dueling UFO Hunters Debuts Jan 30|work=Reality TV World|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}</ref> The episode followed New York Strange Phenomena Investigators (NY-SPI) co-founders Oliver Kemenczky and Ted Davis, along with paranormal researcher Dennis Anderson, as they investigated an alleged alien abduction case in [[Carteret, New Jersey]] and a strange fireball sighting in [[Normandy Beach, New Jersey]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Breaking News - Sci Fi's Development Slate Delivers Intrepid Mix of Inspired Fantasy, Mythical Adventures and Superpowered Comedy {{!}} TheFutonCritic.com |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2007/07/15/sci-fis-development-slate-delivers-intrepid-mix-of-inspired-fantasy-mythical-adventures-and-superpowered-comedy-24929/20070715scifi03/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> The format was similar to a typical ''Ghost Hunters'' episode with most of the program dedicated to the investigation and wrapped up with a review of findings and evidence that was gathered. The pilot episode was reformatted and returned on December 13, 2008, as a special called ''Ny-Spi Investigates'' on [[Investigation Discovery]],<ref>http://www.ny-spi.com/ Ny-Spy Investigates</ref> but was not picked up as a continuing series.\n\n==== ''Ghost Hunters Academy'' ====\n{{Main|Ghost Hunters Academy}}\n\nOn October 23, 2008, ''[[TV Guide]]'' reported that [[Syfy]] would launch a spin-off of the show called ''Ghost Hunters: College Edition'', which would feature \"co-eds\" in the ghost hunter roles.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tvguide.com/News/Ghost-Hunters-College-28608.aspx|title=Ghost Hunters'' Head to College|journal=[[TV Guide]]|date=October 23, 2008|accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref> The show was later named ''Ghost Hunters Academy'' and began airing November 11, 2009. The series features Steve Gonsalves and Dave Tango leading a group of amateur ghost hunters through various investigations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.syfy.com/gha/index.php|title=Home|publisher=}}{{dead link|date=December 2017|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n=== Later series ===\n==== ''Kindred Spirits'' ====\n{{Main|Kindred Spirits (TV series)}}\n''TAPS'' members Adam Berry (also the finalist from ''[[Ghost Hunters Academy]]'') and Amy Bruni left the series in 2014 to start their own program, which was subsequently named ''[[Kindred Spirits (TV series)|Kindred Spirits]]'', which started airing on [[Destination America]] and [[The Learning Channel|TLC]] in 2013 and has aired 3 seasons so far, later moving to [[Travel Channel]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sagers |first1=Aaron |title='Ghost Hunters' Amy Bruni, Adam Berry Exit: Fall Out, Feuds, Predictions Begin |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ghost-hunters-amy-bruni-a_b_5419842 |website=[[Huffington Post]] |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en |date=30 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |last2=Andreeva |first2=Nellie |title=\u2018Ghost Hunters\u2019 Co-Stars Amy Bruni & Adam Berry To Depart, Develop Paranormal Series |url=https://deadline.com/2014/05/ghost-hunters-co-stars-amy-bruni-adam-berry-to-depart-develop-paranormal-series-737158/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en |date=29 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n==== ''Ghost Nation'' ====\n{{Main|Ghost Nation (TV series)}}\nAfter the decision to cut ties with Syfy in 2016 and negotiations to start a new Ghost Hunters series failed, Hawes, Gonsalves and Tango eventually came to decide to focus on efforts to help local investigators on a national level and start a new program ''[[Ghost Nation (TV series)|Ghost Nation]]''. The program has aired on [[Travel Channel]] since October 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title='Ghost Nation' Sees Return of Original 'Ghost Hunters' Jason Hawes, Steve Gonsalves and Dave Tango Tackling the Paranormal |url=https://popculture.com/reality-tv/2019/10/11/ghost-nation-jason-hawes-steve-gonsalves-dave-tango-travel-channel-return-ghost-hunters-paranormal/ |website=Reality TV |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ghost Nation Star Jason Hawes Reveals What to Expect From His New Paranormal Investigation Series |url=https://comicbook.com/horror/2019/10/07/ghost-nation-jason-hawes-jay-hunters-travel-channel-interview/ |website=Horror |accessdate=3 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Truth About 'Ghost Nation' Revealed |url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/ghost-nation-exposed-take-a-behind-the-scenes-look/ |website=[[In Touch Weekly]] |accessdate=3 December 2019 |date=7 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Home media ==\n=== Season releases ===\n\n{{columns\n|col1=\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 1 (The Complete)'' \u2013 (October 18, 2005)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 2, Part 1'' \u2013 (September 19, 2006)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 2, Part 2'' \u2013 (September 19, 2006)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 3, Part 1'' \u2013 (September 9, 2007)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 3, Part 2'' \u2013 (February 26, 2008)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 4, Part 1'' \u2013 (September 7, 2008)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 4, Part 2'' \u2013 (March 17, 2009)\n*''Ghost Hunters \u2014 Season 5, Part 1'' \u2013 (February 2